The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, June 3: Taps ran dry in large parts of the city and its adjoining areas today after civic officials began a massive repair work at 13 points on the network of pipes that carry drinking water to the citys 142 wards.

 This work is aimed at catering to the future demands of the city. Normal water supply should resume from Sunday morning, said mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharya. 

 Calcutta: Sulekha Dutta, 52, died after being knocked down by a private bus on College Street on Saturday morning. Sulekha, a resident of Nilmani Mitra Street, was crossing the road when the bus hit her. An unidentified person was run over by a Qualis at the northern end of the Park Street flyover around 11 pm. Police said the driver lost control of the car and ran up a road divider. The man who died was standing on the divider. 

 Calcutta: Two persons who went inside a dry well in Salt Lake to retrieve a cricket bat were stuck there for half an hour on Saturday. Residents heard their cries for help and rescued them.




